#envpsy #envpsyw7 Cognitive ergonomics refers to if and how people understand their environment and its uses. This switch provides great feedback to its user because it provides straightforward, clear, and distinctive communications on how it is to be used effectively. It has two functions- “on” or “off”- and it is labelled accordingly in order to provide maximum feedback to its user.

#envpsy #envpsyw7 ATTENTION RESTORATION THEORY: This picture is an example of one of Cornell’s many beautiful locations where students can feel close to nature. This relates to the Attention Restoration Theory (ART), which states that interaction with nature heals mental fatigue and recovers capacity to focus attention. Students like myself often go on walks in between classes to reduce anxiety, and being surrounded by nature in Ithaca shows extreme positive effects. Paying attention to the natural environment is involuntary and takes no effort.
